    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1942-03-23T19:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1942-03-23T19:00:00-05:00" n="593"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d593">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">810.20 Defense/2345a: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the Ambassador in Paraguay</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Frost</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1942-03-23T20:00:00-04:00"
                            >March 23, 1942—8 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>84. Under a new contract entered into between the War Department and Pan American
                    Airways it is contemplated to go ahead with construction of airport improvements
                    at Asunción and Concepción in the near future.</p>
                <p>Since it is now well known throughout the American republics that the airport
                    development work of Pan American under the original program was financed by this
                    Government, and in view of the changed situation, it is believed that such
                    negotiations as may be required with the Paraguayan Government should be
                    conducted by this Government rather than through Pan American Airways as was
                    done in the first program. If, in the case of Paraguay, no further permissions
                    or negotiations are necessary, it presumably will be sufficient for you to
                    notify the Paraguayan Government that the construction work will be undertaken
                    soon and at the instance of this Government.</p>
                <p>Specific details of the work contemplated are being sent you by air mail.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Welles</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
